article.headline: Haggerty scores 21 to help Tulsa hold off Rice 85-83

images.name: Tulsa hangs on to beat Rice in chaotic finish
images.caption: The refs go to the monitor to look at a potential foul on a tying attempt by Rice, but rule the game in Tulsa's favor to the dismay of Owls coach Scott Pera.

article.linkText: Haggerty scores 21 to help Tulsa hold off Rice 85-83
article.story: HOUSTON -- — PJ Haggerty scored 19 of his 21 points in the second half to help Tulsa fend off Rice 85-83 on Saturday night. Haggerty added five rebounds for the Golden Hurricane (11-8, 2-5 American Athletic Conference). Cobe Williams added 19 points while shooting 5 for 8 (3 for 5 from 3-point range) and 6 of 10 from the free throw line, and he also had five rebounds, six assists, and four steals. Jared Garcia was 5 of 9 shooting (3 for 6 from 3-point range) to finish with 13 points. Mekhi Mason led the Owls (7-13, 1-6) in scoring, finishing with 19 points, seven assists and three steals. Travis Evee added 15 points for Rice. Max Fiedler also had 14 points, 11 rebounds, seven assists and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
